# UI Title Case & Layout Standards

Use **Title Case** for all user-visible UI copy: screen titles, section headers, field labels, table column headers, and action buttons.

## Title Case examples

- Work Information
- Personal Information
- Save Changes
- Training Scores
- Leave Requests
- Exit Survey

Do **not** use sentence case (`Work information`) or ALL CAPS for section headers.

## Shared utilities

- `formatUILabel()` — `src/utils/titleCase.ts` (auto-applied in `FieldLabel`, `ProfileField`, `FormSection`, `MetricCard`)
- `toTitleCase()` — full string Title Case for API-derived keys
- `UI_COPY` — `src/constants/uiCopy.ts` for common buttons (`Save Changes`, `Cancel`, etc.)
- Layout classes — `src/components/dashboard/ui/uiLayout.ts`
- Section cards — `FormSection`, `FormSubsection` in `FormSection.tsx`
- Action footer — `FormActionBar`

## Layout

- Section spacing: `SECTION_STACK_CLASS` (`space-y-6`)
- Section headers: `SECTION_HEADER_CLASS` + `SECTION_TITLE_CLASS`
- Form fields: `FORM_FIELD_CLASS` + `FieldLabel` (via `forms.tsx`)
- Detail tables: `DETAIL_LABEL_CELL_CLASS` / `DETAIL_VALUE_CELL_CLASS` for Field | Value alignment
- Page shells: `wt-detail-page`, `wt-detail-panel`, `wt-detail-panel__body` for scroll hierarchy
- **Tables**: wrap in `ScrollableTable` (or `wt-scroll-both` shell) + `wt-scrollable-table` on `<table>`; headers stick automatically via `globals.css`
- **Loading**: black `WtLoader` / `SectionLoading` for inline states; `GlobalLoadingOverlay` for fetch/submit/refresh (via `apiClient` + React Query)

## When adding UI

1. Import `UI_COPY` for standard buttons instead of hardcoding strings.
2. Use `FormSection` for grouped form content.
3. Use `toTitleCase()` for dynamic labels derived from API keys when no explicit label exists.
4. Keep label and value columns aligned in read-only profile/detail tables.
